title: User query: Plan description from client LLM
log: Make a Wayang Plan that take the cities in interesting_municipalities_cities textfile and returns all organisations which have a matching municipality in the textfile. The textfile only have cities, but a municipality is usually called something like the city. Output the result in a textfile.

title: Agent: SpecifierAgent Output
log:
Create a Wayang plan that:

- Reads a list of city names from a text file named interesting_municipalities_cities textfile. The file contains only city names.
- Finds all organizations whose municipality matches any city listed in that textfile. (Note: a municipality is usually named the same as the city.)
- Outputs the resulting organizations to a text file.

log.thoughts: Selected textfile containing cities and the organisation table to filter by municipality.

steps.detailed_description: Load the textfile interesting_municipalities_cities, reading one city name per line (Odder, Norddjurs, Faxe, ...).

Join the organisation dataset with the stream of city names on municipality = city_name. Input: organisation table and the list of cities from the textfile. Output: organisations whose municipality matches any city in the list.
Write the filtered organisations to a textfile output named selected_organisations_by_city.txt.

log.thoughts: We read the list of municipalities, perform a join with the Organisation table on municipality, and output the matched organisations to a text file. This uses three steps: load (textfile), join with table, and write output.

title: Class: StepHandler created step dependencies and queue

operations.table: (SELECT organisation_id, organisation_no, active_organisation, name, social_housing_org, municipality FROM organisation) as X

operations.thisKeyUdf: (t: (Integer, Integer, Boolean, String, String, String)) => t._1

log.thoughts: Created a first-step plan with a text file input for cities, a JDBC input for organisations, and a join to filter organisations by municipality matching a city. Included an output to persist results.

operations.table: (SELECT organisation_id, organisation_no, active_organisation, name, social_housing_org, municipality FROM organisation) as X

log.thoughts: Created step 2 plan: reads city list from text file, loads organisations, projects each organisation with its municipality, and joins on municipality/city. IDs kept sequential starting at 1 as there were no prior steps.

title: Class: StepHandler merged subplans to full plan

operations.table: (SELECT organisation_id, organisation_no, active_organisation, name, social_housing_org, municipality FROM organisation) as X
(SELECT organisation_id, organisation_no, active_organisation, name, social_housing_org, municipality FROM organisation) as X

log.thoughts: Refined to read city names from the text file, compare them against the municipalities in the organisation table via a join on municipality/city, and output the matched organisations. This preserves the original intent while ensuring a valid DAG and correct operator usage.

title: Class: PlanMapper Mapped the refined plan finalized for execution

data.table: (SELECT organisation_id, organisation_no, active_organisation, name, social_housing_org, municipality FROM (SELECT organisation_id, organisation_no, active_organisation, name, social_housing_org, municipality FROM organisation) as X) as X
